---
const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'Is FamPass really free?',
    a: 'Yes — completely free to download and use. The free tier shows today\'s events with full details, gives you the map view, and lets you explore curated guides. Premium unlocks the full event calendar weeks ahead, adds calendar sync, unlimited saves, and removes ads.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Where do the events come from?',
    a: 'We aggregate from 30+ trusted sources twice a day: city libraries, parks & recreation departments, museums, ticketing platforms (Eventbrite, Ticketmaster), local venues, and curated community sources. Every listing credits its origin, and the feed refreshes every twelve hours so it stays current.',
  },
  {
    q: 'How do you make sure events are family-friendly?',
    a: 'Two layers: a content filter screens out adult-only listings, 21+ shows, bar crawls, and anything explicitly age-restricted. Then a human reviewer audits flagged or ambiguous events weekly. If something slips through, you can flag it in the app — we\'ll review within 24 hours.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What areas do you cover?',
    a: 'Today: Orange County and Los Angeles, including Irvine, Anaheim, Santa Monica, Pasadena, Long Beach, and dozens more. We\'re actively expanding — sign up in the app to get notified when we launch in your city, and tell us where you\'d like us next.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Can I see events more than a week out?',
    a: 'On Free, you can browse all listings but see full details only for events happening today. Premium unlocks full details for every event, weeks ahead, plus calendar sync so a class series shows up on your family calendar with one tap.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Can I suggest an event or correct a listing?',
    a: 'Yes — there\'s a "Suggest an Event" form in the app\'s More menu, and any listing has a "Report an issue" link. Submissions go to a real person and most are reviewed within 24 hours. Recurring events (a weekly storytime, a class series) are especially welcome.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Will FamPass come to Android?',
    a: 'It\'s on the roadmap. iOS launched first because it lets us iterate faster as a small team. Drop your email in the footer and we\'ll let you know the moment Android is ready.',
  },
  {
    q: 'How do I cancel Premium?',
    a: 'Through your Apple ID: Settings → your name → Subscriptions → FamPass → Cancel. You\'ll keep Premium access until the end of your current billing period. No hoops, no retention scripts.',
  },
];
---
<section class="faq section section--warm" id="faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <div class="section__head">
      <span class="eyebrow">Frequently asked</span>
      <h2>Questions parents actually ask.</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="faq__list">
      {faqs.map(item => (
        <details class="faq__item">
          <summary>
            <span>{item.q}</span>
            <span class="faq__icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="14" height="14"><path d="M4 6l4 4 4-4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <p>{item.a}</p>
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="faq__more">
      <p>Still have questions?</p>
      <a href="/support.html" class="btn btn--ghost btn--sm">Contact support</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .faq__list {
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-line);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .faq__item { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-line-soft); }
  .faq__item:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }

  .faq__item summary {
    list-style: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    padding: 22px 28px;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 1.04rem;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 16px;
    transition: background .12s ease;
  }
  .faq__item summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .faq__item summary:hover { background: var(--color-bg-warm); }

  .faq__icon {
    width: 32px; height: 32px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--color-bg-warm);
    color: var(--color-ink);
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    transition: transform .2s ease, background .12s ease, color .12s ease;
  }
  .faq__item[open] .faq__icon {
    transform: rotate(180deg);
    background: var(--color-accent);
    color: #fff;
  }

  .faq__item p {
    padding: 0 28px 24px;
    color: var(--color-ink-soft);
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 70ch;
  }

  .faq__more {
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 36px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .faq__more p {
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .faq__item summary { padding: 18px 20px; font-size: 1rem; }
    .faq__item p { padding: 0 20px 20px; }
  }
</style>
